#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:5
msgid "fish_add_path - add to the path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:8
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:10
msgid ""
"fish_add_path path ...\n"
"fish_add_path [(-g | --global) | (-U | --universal) | (-P | --path)] [(-m | "
"--move)] [(-a | --append) | (-p | --prepend)] [(-v | --verbose) | (-n | --"
"dry-run)] PATHS ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:19
msgid ""
":program:`fish_add_path` is a simple way to add more components to fish's :"
"envvar:`PATH`. It does this by adding the components either to "
"$fish_user_paths or directly to :envvar:`PATH` (if the ``--path`` switch is "
"given)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:21
msgid ""
"It is (by default) safe to use :program:`fish_add_path` in config.fish, or "
"it can be used once, interactively, and the paths will stay in future "
"because of :ref:`universal variables <variables-universal>`. This is a \"do "
"what I mean\" style command, if you need more control, consider modifying "
"the variable yourself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:23
msgid ""
"Components are normalized by :doc:`realpath <realpath>`. Trailing slashes "
"are ignored and relative paths are made absolute (but symlinks are not "
"resolved). If a component already exists, it is not added again and stays in "
"the same place unless the ``--move`` switch is given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:25
msgid ""
"Components are added in the order they are given, and they are prepended to "
"the path unless ``--append`` is given (if $fish_user_paths is used, that "
"means they are last in $fish_user_paths, which is itself prepended to :"
"envvar:`PATH`, so they still stay ahead of the system paths)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:27
msgid ""
"If no component is new, the variable (:envvar:`fish_user_paths` or :envvar:"
"`PATH`) is not set again or otherwise modified, so variable handlers are not "
"triggered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:29
msgid ""
"If a component is not an existing directory, ``fish_add_path`` ignores it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:32
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:34
msgid "**-a** or **--append**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:35
msgid "Add components to the *end* of the variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:37
msgid "**-p** or **--prepend**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:38
msgid "Add components to the *front* of the variable (this is the default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:40
msgid "**-g** or **--global**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:41
msgid "Use a global :envvar:`fish_user_paths`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:43
msgid "**-U** or **--universal**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:44
msgid ""
"Use a universal :envvar:`fish_user_paths` - this is the default if it "
"doesn't already exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:46
msgid "**-P** or **--path**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:47
msgid "Manipulate :envvar:`PATH` directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:49
msgid "**-m** or **--move**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:50
msgid ""
"Move already-existing components to the place they would be added - by "
"default they would be left in place and not added again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:52
msgid "**-v** or **--verbose**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:53
msgid "Print the :doc:`set <set>` command used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:55
msgid "**-n** or **--dry-run**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:56
msgid "Print the ``set`` command that would be used without executing it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:58
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:59
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:61
msgid ""
"If ``--move`` is used, it may of course lead to the path swapping order, so "
"you should be careful doing that in config.fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:65
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:70
msgid ""
"# I just installed mycoolthing and need to add it to the path to use it.\n"
"> fish_add_path /opt/mycoolthing/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I want my ~/.local/bin to be checked first.\n"
"> fish_add_path -m ~/.local/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I prefer using a global fish_user_paths\n"
"> fish_add_path -g ~/.local/bin ~/.otherbin /usr/local/sbin\n"
"\n"
"# I want to append to the entire $PATH because this directory contains "
"fallbacks\n"
"> fish_add_path -aP /opt/fallback/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I want to add the bin/ directory of my current $PWD (say /home/nemo/)\n"
"> fish_add_path -v bin/\n"
"set fish_user_paths /home/nemo/bin /usr/bin /home/nemo/.local/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I have installed ruby via homebrew\n"
"> fish_add_path /usr/local/opt/ruby/bin"
msgstr ""
